vectorData.altText: 14. Lesions of ventral horn cells of the spinal cord _________ have ipsilateral effects.
That's right!  The ventral horn contains LMNs that innervate ipsilateral targets. Therefore lesions of ventral horn cells of the spinal cord have ipsilateral effects.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

In the brainstem, LMNs form a discontinuous series of motor nuclei associated with some cranial nerves
In the spinal cord, LMNs form the ventral horns.
Remember: the ventral horns are enlarged at cervical and lumbosacral levels to accommodate the LMNs that innervate limbs
LMNs of the ventral horns innervate ipsilateral muscles.
  lesions of spinal LMNs or their axons have ipsilateral effects
